

ls command is used to list the contents in present working directory or mentioned path

syntax : ls  or ls path 
    ex:1.ls 
       2.ls .
       3.ls /programs/xyz/cr

       4.ls -l .
       5.short name of ls -l  is "ll"
       6.we can also use "la ."
          
         ls -l is used to list the all files and directories in your current path in a long format by providing information like owner, size, time, etc.

        7.ls -la also do the same but it provides more information the ls -l

        8.ls -a.  is used to list the all files including hidden files and list the names with beginning with a dot. 
   
         9.ls -F is used for listing the all files and directories by indicating what type of file it is. Slash for the directory and star for the executable files.

          10.ls *.txt - to list the files with the extinction type.
          
         